        <updateDate>2017-03-03T16:23:46Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Probation Officer Protection Act of </b><b>2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to authorize a probation officer to arrest a person (i.e., a person other than the probationer) without a warrant if there is probable cause to believe the person forcibly assaulted or obstructed a probation officer engaged in the performance of official duties.<br /> </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
